comments: Fontecchio (UTA) establishes himself in Martin's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Herro (MIA) and Markkanen (UTA) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Adebayo (MIA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Herro (MIA) brings his forearm towards Markkanen's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Herro (MIA) legally contests Markkanen's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) brings both hands toward Fontecchio (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away to roll.
Vincent (MIA) is moving alongside Horton-Tucker's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the same spot.
Horton-Tucker (UTA) is bracing for the contact from Vincent (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as Horton-Tucker releases away from the contact.
Kessler (UTA) and Adebayo (MIA) briefly engage and disengage as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
Fontecchio (UTA) brings his hands forward towards Butler (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as Butler cuts across the perimeter.
Adebayo (MIA) brings his hands toward Fontecchio (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away to roll.

Replay review of the foul called on Vincent (MIA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Fontecchio (UTA) extends his hands into Vincent and delivers contact that re-routes Vincent into Horton-Tucker (UTA).
Kessler (UTA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Agbaji (UTA) is moving alongside Herro's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs as Herro loses control of the ball on his own.
Vincent (MIA) brings his forearm forward towards Agbaji's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) absorbs the contact to his chest and avoids making contact with Agbaji's (UTA) arm as he contests the driving shot attempt.
Fontecchio (UTA) commits a take foul on Adebayo (MIA).
Butler (MIA) brings his forearm towards Markkanen's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Markkanen (UTA) brings his forearm towards Butler's (MIA) upper body and marginal contact occurs as Markkanen releases from the contact.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Markkanen's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
